title: Bug 4121 - JarExporter causes out of Sync
description: When exporting a directory (project) and placing the exported JAR file in the same directory (project), overwriting the JAR file for a second time results in an out of sync message.
OB: When I exported a directory (project) and placed the exported JAR in the same directory, I received an out of sync message when attempting to overwrite the JAR file the second time.
SR:
To reproduce this issue, follow these steps:  
1. Export a directory as a JAR file.  
2. Place the exported JAR file in the same directory.  
3. Attempt to overwrite the JAR file by exporting the directory again.  
4. Observe the out of sync message.
